  "body": "## Simple Summary\r\nconverting bytes should be given more convertible types, such as bytes32 to bytes[1] (fixed type)\r\n\r\n## Abstract\r\nyou can only convert bytes32 to int128 and bytes256, making it hard to trim bytes32 (such as sha3 digest) into bytes[x]\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nthis would be in line with the goal to increase code legibility without using slicing\r\n\r\n## Specification\r\n\r\nthis implementation is compilable in Solidity through casting\r\n\r\n```\r\n// hash\r\n                bytes32 hashOfSerialNumber = keccak256(serialNumber);\r\n\r\n// get first 8 bits as as 1 byte, uint8 used in Sol but uint256 viable when smaller uint not available\r\n                bytes1 truncatedHash = bytes1(hashOfSerialNumber);\r\n                uint8 unsignedTruncatedHash = uint8(truncatedHash);\r\n```\r\n\r\nsuggested syntax\r\n\r\n`convert(bytes32, bytes[1]) -> covertedVar`\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Backwards Compatibility\r\nno expected compatibility errors\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)\r\n",
